Numerous studies (several hundred; see 
 Adamowski, 2016–2020 and the literature cited therein) have been devoted to the ecology, biology, and genetics of this species (e.g., 
 Antlfinger, 1989; 
 Schmitt, Ehrhardt & Swartz, 1985; 
 Donohue & Schmitt, 1999; 
 Donohue et al., 2000; 
 Zika, 2009; 
 Tabak & Von Wettberg, 2008; 
 Day, Pellicer & Kynast, 2012). However, a review of the available literature showed a scarcity of data on seed size and a complete lack of information describing the morphological variation of the seed coat of 
 I. capensis (
 Schemske, 1978; 
 Waller, 1982; 
 Simpson, Leck & Parker, 1985; 
 Bojňanský & Fargašová, 2007).
